  ## Common Issues & Fixes

  ### "Port 1234 is already in use"

  **Quick fix:**
  <div class="code-block">
    <div class="code-block-header">
      <span class="code-block-lang">Bash</span>
      <button class="code-block-copy">Copy</button>
    </div>
    <pre><code># Kill the process using port 1234
# Windows
netstat -ano | findstr :1234
taskkill /PID [PID] /F

# Mac/Linux
lsof -i :1234
kill -9 [PID]</code></pre>
  </div>

  ### "Module not found"

  **Quick fix:**
  <div class="code-block">
    <div class="code-block-header">
      <span class="code-block-lang">Bash</span>
      <button class="code-block-copy">Copy</button>
    </div>
    <pre><code># Reinstall dependencies
rm -rf node_modules package-lock.json
npm install</code></pre>
  </div>

  ### "Invalid API key"

  **Quick fix:**
  1. Check your `.env` file
  2. Make sure API key starts with `gsk_`
  3. No extra spaces or quotes
  4. Generate new key at [console.groq.com](https://console.groq.com)

  ### Agent not responding

  **Quick fix:**
  1. Check Terminal 2 for errors
  2. Verify Groq API key in `.env`
  3. Restart agent: `Ctrl+C` then `npm run agent`

